title: Queensland road toll: Cyclist dies after Chapel Hill crash, children hurt in Chermside incident | Geelong Advertiser
text:
Queensland road toll: Cyclist dies after Chapel Hill crash, children hurt in Chermside incident Clare Armstrong, The Courier-Mail February 18, 2017 4:45pm 
FOUR children have been taken to hospital with minor injuries after a crash outside one of Brisbane’s biggest shopping centres. 
Two vehicles collided at the intersection of Murphy Rd and Kittyhawke Drive, outside Chermside Shopping Centre, about 1.30pm today. 
The children aged 1, 2, 4 and 5 were taken to Lady Cilento Hospital with their mother, however it is understood their injuries were all minor. 
Meanwhile, a cyclist has died in hospital following a serious crash in Brisbane’s western suburbs early yesterday morning. 
The 50-year-old was involved in a collision with a car on Moggill Rd near Chapel Hill Rd at Chapel Hill about 5.15am. 
The 21-year-old driver of the car was not injured. 
The Forensic Crash Unit is investigating.
